bio: To Aditi, yoga goes beyond movement and can bring freedom and joy into life. Having lived and practiced yoga in India and NYC, Aditi’s style of teaching is anchored in tradition, creativity, fun, and flowing, challenging her students to grow from the inside out. She has been named one of NYC’s best instructors, led exciting events like a live 2000+ person class in Time Square, and helped to launch Peloton Yoga and Meditation in 2018! Deeply connected to storytelling and music, Aditi shines when teaching artist series classes, and her own signature series Flow and Let Go.
background: Yoga is a practice that allows us to thread together the external with the internal - the physical workings with the mental, emotional, spiritual.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'Yoga is a direction - you are aiming for a posture. You don’t have to get there today, but you do have to start, you do have to try. When I began practicing, I could not get my hands to the ground.'], ['Outside of Peloton ', 'I’m a total nerd about health and love to read about science. I also love to travel the world and I lived in Mumbai for a few years and love it there. I’ve climbed Kilimanjaro, and love to trek and hike.'], ['', '']]
quote: Practice makes progress.
name: Aditi Shah

bio: Adrian is a powerhouse instructor with an unexpected tender side. A native New Yorker with bold Bronx energy, Adrian is a competitive sprinter—but he’s not all speed and strength. Adrian's lighthearted sense of humor is what really shines through his coaching. His goal is to encourage others and bring joy through fitness. When he’s not at the gym, you can find Adrian perfecting his craft behind the camera. Adrian is a passionate photographer and finds peace in the creative process.
short_bio: Adrian is a powerhouse instructor with an unexpected tender side. A native New Yorker with bold Bronx energy, Adrian is a competitive sprinter—but he’s not all speed and strength. His lighthearted sense of humor shines through his coaching.
background: Working out should feel good! My goal is to empower people to form healthy habits to carry with them for the rest of their lives. I will challenge you, then hit you with positivity. At the end of the day, I want to bring you joy!
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I encourage you to embrace being uncomfortable. That’s where growth happens. I try not to take myself too seriously, though. My workouts are tough, but I like to lead with humor. I want you to leave with a smile!'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'Photography has been a growing passion of mine. Fitness requires so much energy, and photography helps me slow down and appreciate small moments. I also love to cook too, because I love to eat!'], ['', '']]
quote: “Never give up because great things take time.”
name: Adrian Williams

bio: All Instructors
short_bio: All Instructors
background: All Instructors
name: All Instructors

bio: I foolishly thought that rowing was like running—just on the water instead of on the track—and hopped in a boat my freshman year. Fortunately, I've never been so happy to be so wrong. I was hooked from that first moment and have dedicated the last 15 years to this sport. I can't wait to share my enthusiasm for rowing with the Peloton community.
short_bio: Alex comes to Peloton Row via the World Championships and the Olympics—but you’ll never meet a more humble, enthusiastic guy. When you row with Alex, you’re guaranteed to learn something new.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', "I never want Members to feel like they have to get through class. I want you to feel that it's an opportunity to push for a little more and find out something about yourself."], ['Outside of Peloton? ', 'In my time away from the studio, you can find me scoping out the best new Thai food in town, listening to phenomenal movie soundtracks, or building classic LEGO sets—there is always more space in the apartment!'], ['', '']]
quote: “It doesn’t matter what I do—it matters what I bring out in other people.”
name: Alex Karwoski

bio: Alex Toussaint has a love for fitness, teamwork and discipline rooted in his military school background. With his eye always on the prize, Alex uses the power of positivity to motivate Members to confront their limitations and push past them. In his class, you can expect a well-structured ride, and to walk out feeling his mantra in your bones: “Feel good, look good, do better.”
short_bio:
"Feel good. Look good. Do better! 
… Trust the Process!"
music_bio: Check out a sample of Alex’s current class playlist.
background: I approach all my classes like it might be my last one. Watching Members become the best version of themselves truly inspires me to give it my all every ride I teach.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'Using my military background, I push my Members to their full potential at all times. I want Members to approach my workout like an athlete, and leave feeling like a champion.\r\n'], ['Outside of Peloton', "When I’m off the Bike I’m on the basketball court or gym. Fitness isn't just my hobby, it’s my life!"], ['', '']]
quote:
Feel good. Look good. Do better! 
… Trust the Process!
name: Alex Toussaint

bio: As a model, dancer, certified health coach, host of the Brooklyn Nets, runner, and the founder of fitness lifestyle brand Love Squad, Ally really does it all. At Peloton as in all of her pursuits, Ally’s goal is to lead by example while empowering people to approach wellness and fitness in a positive light. When she’s not on the Peloton Bike, you can find her flexing her entrepreneurial muscles, or enjoying a good doughnut.
short_bio: They say the early bird gets the worm, but the early bird only gets whatever is left over from the hustlers.
music_bio: Check out a sample of Ally’s current class playlist.
background: My life goal is to remind the world that we all have one life to live, and together we should live it to the fullest. I believe that what connects us most is the power of sweat, and physically working through things as a team.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'We ride to become boss of the Bike and to remind ourselves that we are the boss of our lives. My classes are designed to make you feel proud and uplifted, both on and off the bike.'], ['Outside of Peloton', "I always try find the right balance of fun and work, knowing they don't have to be different things. Off the Bike I love donuts, tennis, basketball, karaoke and parties."], ['', '']]
quote: They say the early bird gets the worm, but the early bird only gets whatever is left over from the hustlers.
name: Ally Love

bio: Andy takes a technique-centered approach to fitness, drawing on his experience as an accomplished former gymnast and pole vaulter in his home state of Connecticut. A celebrated personal trainer in NYC before joining Peloton, Andy is inspired by the world-class fitness and strength coaches who taught him, and brings his breadth of training knowledge to every workout.
short_bio: "Fight Fatigue with Focus."
background: My inspiration for teaching is rooted in helping others improve their lives through fitness, as other coaches have done for me, now it’s my turn to pay it forward.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I want members to approach my class with an intent to be challenged and grow. I focus on technique and ensure that there is a purpose behind everything I ask of you.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'My training also includes gymnastics, kettlebells, Olympic weightlifting, Muay Thai kickboxing, and yoga. I also enjoy watching documentaries, meditation, reading, and listening to Podcasts.'], ['', '']]
quote: Fight Fatigue with Focus.
name: Andy Speer

bio: When Anna first turned to yoga, she felt a switch turn on inside of her. As she built a deeper connection with her mind and body, she began accomplishing things she never knew possible. Moved to share the transformative properties of the practice with others, Anna dove head first into yoga. Anna has crafted a unique teaching style that uses movement and music to help her Members connect to the same healing properties of yoga that she has experienced over the years. Anna is a prominent teacher trainer, workshop leader and instructor in NYC.
short_bio: “Look for balance but always be willing to fall”
background: My classes combine heat building movement with precise, focused instruction for Members to find stability and space in their bodies and minds. Watching Members grow and thrive on the mat and in their lives is what inspires me to teach!
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I aim to inspire people to do their best and let go of the results. Yoga is not a competition or performance, it’s just for you (how great is that?). It’s a tool to strengthen your relationship with yourself.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'When I’m not standing on my hands, you can catch me traveling the world whenever, and wherever I can. I enjoy being in nature, hiking, biking and just walking around and taking it all in.'], ['', '']]
quote: Look for balance but always be willing to fall.
name: Anna Greenberg

bio: I’m a first-generation college student, and I’m proud to have broken multiple glass ceilings: I’m a black woman who has won rowing championships, I hold an advanced degree, and I’m a published author. I also run my own rowing academy! I like to keep busy.
short_bio: Ash’s classes are always a party—but when the red lipstick comes out, you’re in for a serious sweat. She’s a Big Ten champion, a seasoned coach, and she instills positivity into every stroke. With Ash, you’ll always leave feeling brighter.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', "I’m excited to bring a party on a rower. We can be weird and goofy and get an amazing workout. If you're gonna sparkle, then sparkle! I’ll challenge you to bust through the glass ceiling, and kick your butt with a smile."], ['Outside of Peloton', "I'm learning to play the ukulele right now. It is red and her name is Ruby. And I love documentaries. Family and community are important to me—I love spending time with my loved ones, and being a cool auntie! "], ['', '']]
quote: “I’m a bull—so when we see red, we boogie!”
name: Ash Pryor

bio: As a refugee child, Assal was often made to feel like she had to prove herself more than others. But her mother always taught her about the power of being herself. A former weightlifter and police officer, she’s learned that true strength is both vulnerability and the ability to get comfortable in the discomfort of hard work. Because a strong body starts with a strong mindset. Now, she’s bringing her passion, precision, dedication, and drive to classes that will motivate you to strengthen your muscles and your mind. She wants to show you that the only person you need to prove anything to is yourself—and that once you embrace this, you’ll be unstoppable.
short_bio: A former weightlifter and police officer, Assal Arian knows that a strong body starts with a strong mindset. She wants to show you that the only person you need to prove anything to is yourself—once you embrace this, you’ll be unstoppable.
background: I’ve been told I’m too ambitious, too small, too Persian. But it just made me stronger, because my mum showed me the power of being me. And this is what I teach in my classes—the only person you need to prove anything to is yourself.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate others?', 'There is so much power in being a beginner—when you’re ready and motivated to learn is when you really grow. I make my classes a place where everyone feels empowered to try new things and see what they can achieve.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I love music. Any kind of music. From reggaeton to hip hop, house, electro to dancehall and flamenco. It helps me lose myself in the moment and find motivation in different places.'], ['', '']]
quote: I’m always trying something new, finding new challenges, getting out of my comfort zone, and working to improve.
name: Assal Arian

bio: Becs joins Peloton from London as an accomplished distance runner and coach who uses the sport as a way to explore the world. From adventurous trails, tropical beaches, and exotic volcanoes, to sub-3:00 marathons and demanding ultramarathons, she’s run across the globe and can’t wait for her next journey on the Peloton Tread. When teaching, Becs shares wisdom from her own training experience to help inspire everyone from first time runners to seasoned athletes. No matter how experienced you are, you’ll leave her class smiling and proud, energized to tackle your next challenge.
short_bio: "Challenge yourself, and be determined to thrive."
background: My inspiration comes from running all around the world! I want to teach the people in my class to love the way running makes them feel. My approach is tough, but I’ll always run with a smile because my passion for the sport is so alive.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I share a lot of my own personal training experiences to relate to people in my classes. I want Members to see that we have the same goals, and are on a journey together.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I train for my own goals, setting myself up for whatever my next race may be. I adore spending time eating my way around cities, so moving to NYC has been a dream and I keep finding amazing new places everywhere I go.'], ['', '']]
quote: Challenge yourself, and be determined to thrive.
name: Becs Gentry

bio: Growing up, Ben was an accomplished athlete who was always looking for the opportunity to run, ride, kick a ball or compete. Working at a prestigious finance firm, Ben found himself daydreaming about his days on the field and in the gym. That inspired him to begin training clients as a side hustle. He quickly gained momentum and decided to take a leap of faith to leave finance behind to pursue his true passion in fitness. Ben is excited to connect through his love of music, coach with Peloton Members around the world, and become a part of their story as they move through challenges on and off the Bike. Ben is based in the UK and teaches cycling & strength.
short_bio: Work hard in silence, let progress be your noise.
background: I love fitness because it has a wonderful way of breaking down barriers for people.
ordered_q_and_as: [[' How Do You Motivate?\r\n', 'I love having the opportunity to change someone’s mindset and self-belief. I love to inspire. I love to educate people so they feel fully in control of their own progress.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I found my passion for training through track and field, and have completed marathons and ultra endurance events. Outside of fitness, I’m a huge fan of live music and travel, and am always on the hunt for my next meal.'], ['', '']]
quote: Work hard in silence, let progress be your noise.
name: Ben Alldis

bio: Benny was born in the gym–he lives and breathes fitness. When he's not partying on his Peloton Bike, wowing you with his positive vibes, he's training with his friends and getting inspired by other workouts. Only music can inspire him as much as exercise. And he knows that you get the best out of yourself when you just have some fun. So be yourself and experience how to turn any workout into a party.
short_bio: Benny comes from a real sports family and spent half his life in gyms. In his rides, he combines endurance and technique with fun and entertainment. When you train with Benny, every workout becomes a party.
background: In my workouts you can be anything, but most of all you can be yourself. I want everyone in my rides to have a good time. That's why I became a Peloton instructor.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate others?', 'Fun and entertainment are the most important things in my workouts. I want everyone to enjoy every ride. The rest will just come naturally.'], ['Outside of Peloton', "My friends are the most important thing to me. I love fitness and music. If I can combine those three things, then I'm the happiest person in the world."], ['', '']]
quote: Working out with you all is my party.
name: Benny Adami

bio: If there’s one thing that really motivates former boxing instructor Bradley, it’s having the odds stacked against him. The moment someone says he can’t do something, well, that’s all he needs to hear to go out and do it! It’s why he’s often been labelled a rebel as he always manages to find a way to overcome life’s obstacles by doing things his way. After a decade in New York, Bradley is now back in the UK to bring his unique blend of British charm and eternally optimistic attitude to the London cycling studio. He’s a big believer that life is an adventure we shouldn’t take too seriously, so expect him to keep you smiling through his sweat-drenched sessions on the Bike.
short_bio: Boxing fan Bradley believes you’re never beaten, however big the challenge. It’s this approach to life combined with his infectious smile and a love of putting fun at the heart of his classes that will keep you coming back.
background: I want Members to leave my classes with a smile on their face KNOWING they’ve got the beating of whatever challenges they may be facing. However much of an underdog you may feel, there is always a way over that hill.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', "FUN is important to me! It becomes really hard to stick to something if you're not enjoying yourself, so I’ll push past whatever excuses you've got, but because you're being equally entertained, you'll hardly notice."], ['Outside of Peloton\r\n', "I'm a keen traveller, animal lover and meditator. I've been called a rebel because I love proving people wrong, so you’re welcome to challenge me, but beware, I won't just beat you, I'll also post about it on Instagram!"], ['', '']]
quote: Sometimes you have to fight more than once to win it
name: Bradley Rose

bio:
Callie radiates sunshine. She comes from a large family of athletes, but broke the mold to pursue dance. Years of rigorous ballet training taught her discipline, grace and strength. Her knowledge of technique and emphasis on quality of movement extends to her classes. 

Callie’s workouts are tough, but she’ll make you feel good after every class.
background: Everyone is welcome in my class. I want you to feel comfortable and confident after we work out together.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', 'We can accomplish anything we put our mind to by instilling confidence. Show up as yourself, and I’ll guide you the rest of the way. Expect to work hard, laugh a little and leave with an undeniable sense of self worth.'], ['Outside of Peloton? ', 'When I’m not at Peloton, you can find me shopping in the pillow aisle or throwing punches in the gym. Nothing makes me happier than spending time with loved ones in the comfort of my own home. '], ['', '']]
quote: “Believe in yourself, and you're halfway there.”
name: Callie Gullickson

bio: Introducing Camila Ramón, Peloton’s newest cycling instructor. Camila is teaching in both Spanish and English, and she’s bringing a whole new energy and positivity to Peloton. You’ll hear it right away with her music choices, and you’ll see it right away with her dance moves. Camila instills positive, powerful perspectives and approaches to life and relationships with fitness, so you’ll never feel more confident than when you ride with her.
background: I was born in Argentina and grew up in Miami. Family is everything to me. I’m deeply connected to my community, and I bring that energy with me to every class, every day. Come ride with me!
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', 'I motivate through passion and positivity. I care about every person in my class. I teach you to push boundaries. I want you to discover your strength, and after class, I want you to feel like you can take on anything!'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'Being outdoors centers me. I love hiking, running and camping with my husband and my pup Rex. I love spending time with my vibrant family and eating dulce de leche while binge-watching netflix.'], ['', '']]
quote: Juntos en esta comunidad somos imparables.
name: Camila Ramón

bio: As the oldest of four siblings, Charlotte has always looked after everyone else. Looking out for and loving herself was something she had to learn first. To her, working out is self-care. As a trained doctor, she knows that every time you work out, you're doing something good for you. Expect Bike classes full of power and positivity—for Charlotte, limits exist only to be overcome.
short_bio: For Charlotte, limits only exist to be overcome. No matter your fitness level, as a trained doctor, she’ll help you discover what you're capable of. Join her in her powerful classes and finish every ride with a proud smile.
background: As a doctor, I know my body inside out. But only through fitness did I learn to also love myself. Don’t be afraid to love yourself and to be proud of you. That’s what I want to pass on to our Members.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'Fitness is my medicine—it has the power to change your life. Every time we’re working out together, you’re doing something good for yourself. Leave your life behind, forget all expectations and just give your best.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'From opera to rock to techno–music plays a big part in my life. And that includes both dancing to the sounds of my favorite DJ and relaxing on the couch to my favorite album.'], ['', '']]
quote: Let’s find our limits—and then challenge them together.
name: Charlotte Weidenbach

bio: Chelsea has traveled a unique path to bring her expression of yoga to both the tenured yogi and those who never believed the practice was for them. Chelsea received her Ph.D. in Educational Studies, making it her life's work to study the positive impact that yoga has on communities. Chelsea believes that practicing yoga connects you more deeply to yourself and the world around you, making you happier and healthier in your daily life. Chelsea's teaching style is creative, challenging and compassionate, making you feel at home with her as you build strength and confidence.
short_bio: Chelsea believes that practicing yoga connects you more deeply to yourself and the world around you. Her teaching style is creative, challenging and compassionate, making you feel at home with her while you build confidence and strength.
background: My intention is to create an environment that leaves Members with a strong sense of belonging and accomplishment. I am inspired by how yoga, music and soulful storytelling can take us on a journey closer to ourselves.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I empower you to embrace the body you are in! Yoga is an opportunity to pour love back into yourself, and can travel with you off the mat and into your life in the form of strength, peace, presence and wisdom.  '], ['Outside of Peloton', 'As a Ph.D. and former school teacher, I bring yoga and education to others. I created a tuition-free space for teen girls to read, write poetry, practice yoga and build a community called Yoga, Literature & Art Camp. '], ['', '']]
quote: I want to be someone people relate to. I’ll encourage you as I push you.
name: Chelsea Jackson Roberts

bio: Christine D’Ercole is a decorated track cyclist who brings this expertise to every Peloton class. Grounded in science, music, grit and grace, Christine believes that at all times you have two tools at your disposal: your breath and your inner monologue. In her class, you can expect Christine to empower Members to break through self-imposed limitations, and embrace their authentic selves and strength, both on and off the Bike.
short_bio: "I AM. I CAN. I WILL. I DO."
music_bio: Check out a sample of Christine’s current class playlist.
background: My classes are grounded in science, grit and grace. I will give you structured formats rooted in 20 years of competitive cycling experience set to playlists that push you farther than you thought possible.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?\r\n', 'Every class is an opportunity to put something across the finish line and make yourself proud. By showing up, turning it up and not giving up, we practice real-life skills that translate off the Bike.'], ['Outside of Peloton\r\n', 'BIKE RACING!, Wordshop™, writing, cooking, fine wine, scuba diving and photography.'], ['', '']]
quote: I AM. I CAN. I WILL. I DO.
name: Christine D'Ercole

bio: Growing up in Hamburg, Cliff’s first love was football–until music came along. In fact, his love of hip hop saw him become the first German rapper to make it to the semi-finals of the ‘Voice of Germany’. Given he’s used to performing on a stage under the bright lights, it’s no wonder he feels so at home in the Peloton studio. As a Peloton Instructor, Cliff’s passion and energy mean you leave his class not only feeling like you’ve had a great workout, but also feeling re-energised and ready to hit all the high notes. Cliff rides in our London studio and does Bike and Bootcamp classes in German.
short_bio: As a Peloton Instructor, Cliff’s passion and energy help you leave his class not only feeling like you’ve had a great workout, but also being re-energised and ready to take on whatever life has in store for you.
background: I’m inspired by the synergy of music and fitness, it gives me an energy that I just have to pass on. Everyone feels that in every single class I give.
ordered_q_and_as: [['HOW DO YOU MOTIVATE?', 'As an athlete, praise and positive encouragement have always driven me to push myself beyond my limits and perform at my best. With this power, I want to motivate everyone to achieve more and look for fewer excuses. '], ['OUTSIDE OF PELOTON', "When I'm not on the Peloton stage, I spend as much time as possible with my family. My wife and daughter mean everything to me."], ['', '']]
quote: No excuses - Don't look for excuses, find solutions.
name: Cliff Dwenger

bio: A former professional dancer, Cody brings energy, movement and authenticity to everything he does. Born in the West but raised in the South, Cody always dreamed of a life in the big city. Now that he proudly calls NYC home–and the best city in the world–he strives to be the best version of himself while inspiring Members to be the same. Cody reminds everyone in his class to push themselves, but have a good time doing it, because we all need to have a little more fun.
short_bio: "Can I do this? ABSOLUTELY!"
music_bio: Check out a sample of Codys current class playlist.
background: Success happens when you allow yourself to be in the present moment —  when we truly let go of any regret of the past or fear of the future.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?\r\n', 'If I am not living my truth in everything I do, then I am not doing it right. I want Members to have fun while they’re working out, and remember that even though it’s challenging, "It’s not that deep!”'], ['Outside of Peloton\r\n', 'Outside of Peloton I love to travel and discover the world. Because of my busy life in NYC, I love to find balance and serenity through my meditation practice.'], ['', '']]
quote: Can I do this? ABSOLUTELY!
name: Cody Rigsby

bio: Raised in Florida, schooled in Tennessee, steeped in southern California and heat-tested in Texas, Denis brings 14 years of fitness leadership to Peloton. With an athletic history ranging from college football to aerial acrobatics, and a musical taste to match, Denis will keep you moving, grooving and guessing what comes next.
short_bio: “Learn to love the skin you’re in.”
music_bio: Check out a sample of Denis’ current class playlist.
background: This bike gives us an opportunity to reclaim our natural athleticism, even if only for a few minutes each day, which leads naturally to a renewed self image and that feeling of athleticism that had long been lying dormant.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I use music and personal stories to connect deeply between the workout, the people in the room and the Members around the world. I want to inspire people to explore their own abilities with my guidance and experience.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I surf, practice yoga, snowboard, skateboard, hike, play guitar, read historical nonfiction, lift weights, watch college football (FSU) and look for chances to stamp my passport.'], ['', '']]
quote: Learn to love the skin you’re in
name: Denis Morton

bio: Emma Lovewell is a Martha’s Vineyard native and a woman of all trades. She’s spent much of her career in fitness and wellness as a professional dancer, dance coach, fitness model, personal trainer and pilates instructor. Emma was also a DJ, and brings this love of music to her teaching style at Peloton. She’s passionate about movement and connecting the heavy beats of her playlists to each ride she teaches. After class, expect to feel like you just stepped off the dance floor.
short_bio: "I love you, but I’m going to push you."
music_bio: Check out a sample of Emma’s current class playlist.
background: I always try to find the perfect combination of training and entertainment so that class will fly by, and you won’t even realize how hard you just pushed yourself.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I want people to feel lighter when they finish my class; whether it’s leaving behind a puddle of sweat, or letting go of negative thoughts or feelings. Don’t ever miss an opportunity to get stronger.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I come from a creative family of entrepreneurs so I play the piano, enjoy painting watercolors, cooking, gardening, adventuring and traveling. I always need a creative outlet so I have a lot of hobbies!'], ['', '']]
quote: I love you, but I’m going to push you.
name: Emma Lovewell

bio: Erik brings the joy of sport and fitness to Peloton. Growing up a passionate soccer player and fan, Erik learned how to be a positive leader and team player. This ultimately guided him to a career in athletic and personal training. Erik loves helping others achieve their goals, and believes that, no matter, what getting healthy and strong should always be lighthearted and fun.
background: I want to make people feel good—about themselves and about their lives. By working hard and laughing together on the Bike, we’ll channel each other’s positive energy and discover more confidence along the way.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'By reminding you that you are not alone! I’m sweating and being challenged right alongside you every minute of class, and my goal is to keep you smiling the whole time.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'When I’m not recharging, I try to enjoy every minute of life. I love to see the world, party with friends and eat ice cream'], ['', '']]
quote: Sport is for everyone.
name: Erik Jäger

bio: Hannah grew up in Portland, Oregon and came to New York City to dance. She is passionate about guiding others’ fitness journeys and watching them evolve. A kick-your-butt drill sergeant, fiery New York dancer and a West Coast flower child all at once, Hannah is dedicated to a teaching style that empowers people to appreciate how strong they are, and how to protect that strength with stretching when they hop off the Bike and head out into the world.
short_bio: "You are a rockstar. Treat yourself accordingly."
music_bio: Check out a sample of Hannah’s current class playlist.
background: Wanna hear a joke? Thinking you have limits. I teach for that moment when you realize what I've known from the start: you can do this, and you're stronger than you know.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'Treat your body like it belongs to someone you love. Admire your strength, and take time to recover. And always ask yourself, #didyoustretchtho?'], ['Outside of Peloton', "I'm on a quest to hang upside down from every ceiling on silks, hug every tree in the Northeast, and dance down every street in Manhattan."], ['', '']]
quote: You are a rockstar. Treat yourself accordingly.
name: Hannah Corbin

bio: Hannah’s electric spirit empowers others to show up and celebrate every milestone. Active from a young age, she seized every moment to push herself past what others deemed impossible. From her time spent as a competitive triple jumper to training alongside Olympic athletes, Hannah grew an appreciation for the power and strength hidden within. This passion eventually led her to fall in love with making exercise fun for everyone. Through music, sweat and cycling, she loves to show people that there is magic in every moment. All you have to do is show up! Hannah is based in the UK and teaches live rides from our London studio.
short_bio: quote
background: If you want to learn more about who you are, you have to take yourself to places you’ve never been. Come ride with me and take your body and mind on an adventure in a fun and challenging way!
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', "I like to champion Members for the big and small victories they create. In a world where we are always blinded by what we aren't, I want to remind people of who they are and what they already have."], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I love London, especially the east. I like cycling or walking down the canal in summer, hitting a live music or comedy night, checking out an exhibition or getting down at a decent club night.'], ['', '']]
quote: “Own your body. Challenge your mind.”
name: Hannah Frankson

bio: As a talent recruiter for the Voice of Germany and fitness instructor, Jeffrey has learned how to get the best out of different talents. As a Peloton running instructor, he wants you to get to know and love yourself in a new way and become the best version of yourself. Look forward to workouts full of motivation, passion, pushing beats and finishing every run with a smile on your face.
short_bio: For Jeffrey, running is a journey to oneself. He wants you to know and love yourself better workout after workout. Whatever your fitness level, together with Jeffrey you will finish every run with a smile.
background: When I discovered running, I got to know myself in a new way and I discovered that all the power I need is already within me. I want to show you, how to unleash that power within you, becoming the best version of yourself.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', "Running has the power to put a smile on anyone's face. Metre by metre, you get to know and love yourself anew. I want us to experience this together and let the music guide us."], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I love to laugh—preferably with my family, my friends or my godchild. When I have some time to myself, I meditate or relax with a good podcast.  And of course music. I love music and need it like the air I breathe.'], ['', '']]
quote: WORKING OUT IS LIKE WATER TO ME. YOU’VE GOT TO STAY HYDRATED.
name: Jeffrey McEachern

bio: Jenn Sherman took her first indoor cycling class more than a decade ago and was instantly hooked. As Peloton’s very first cycling instructor, Jenn came to NYC from her hometown in New Jersey, where she’d been selling out studios for years. Jenn brings a focused intensity to every class she teaches, showing Members what they’re made of with her empowering playlists you just can’t help but sing along to.
short_bio: "JFDI!!! Or (JUST F**KING DO IT) No excuses. Simple, direct and to the point. Just like ME!"
music_bio: Check out a sample of Jenn's current class playlist.
background: Being able to make a difference in people’s lives is the inspiration. I draw from the strength, motivation and the incredible energy I receive every day from my riders.
ordered_q_and_as:
[['How Do You Motivate?
', 'Leave the bulls**t outside the door and take this window of time for YOU. Walk in ready to work hard, sweat hard, sing hard and leave the room feeling empowered by what you just accomplished.'], ['Outside of Peloton
', 'I am the mom to two teenagers, who are the center of my world. When I’m not running in circles with my family, I can be found relaxing at the beach with friends, or working on my next killer playlist.
'], ['', '']]
quote: JFDI!!! Or (JUST F**KING DO IT) No excuses. Simple, direct and to the point. Just like ME!
name: Jenn Sherman

bio: London born and raised, Jermaine is driven by the belief that you make your own opportunities. From working as a professional dancer through building a brand as a fitness coach and now in his dream role at Peloton, movement has always been at the heart of everything he does. But this isn’t just going with the flow—this is movement powered by a hunger to hustle. It’s about developing the determination and skill to navigate obstacles and always keep pushing forwards. With his focus and natural warmth, he helps people step out of their comfort zone but in tune with their own bodies—bringing them together to train hard whilst growing in confidence.
short_bio: Jermaine’s drive and positivity are a force to be reckoned with. He’s passionate about helping you work hard today for a better tomorrow and move forward no matter what, and his classes will leave you feeling ready to take on anything.
background: I want to empower you to take on anything you set your mind to. Together, we’re going to keep moving no matter what, fuelled by big tunes and plenty of positivity—because who says the hustle can’t be fun?
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I inspire Members through my positive energy—tackling tough workouts with a smile on my face. I want everyone to feel like whatever they have going on in their lives, they can find a safe space to just let go.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'l like to lift weights and challenge myself by learning new skills. I also enjoy taking my dog for walks around London and exploring new countries—especially the Caribbean, where I can add to my extensive rum collection!'], ['', '']]
quote: Train today for a better tomorrow
name: Jermaine Johnson

bio: Jess is a charismatic instructor with a boundless energy and passion for movement. With a background in dance, performance and fitness, Jess grew up down South and moved to NYC to commit to a career in wellness. Jess’s self-proclaimed sassy and spicy personality make her Bike and Tread classes uplifting and full of exciting surprises. Jess is committed to helping people heal from the inside out, and she believes that this community is the perfect place to start that journey. Her focus is to partner with motivated individuals looking to transform their lives — and together, they burn.
short_bio: "I am the magma from the Earth’s core that ignites the fire of transformation in myself and others."
music_bio: Check out a sample of Jess's current class playlist.
background: Sweat is the special sauce that bridges the gap between our inner and outer worlds. I approach every ride as an opportunity to change my life. We are transforming together, in real time.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?\r\n', 'I lead from the perspective that you are whole now, and everything you need to get through the ride, your day, or whatever you’re confronting, is already inside of you.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I have a customized wellness transformation program called MindFULL3 centered around nourishment, movement and process. Through conversation and communal support, we help you design the life you were meant to lead.'], ['', '']]
quote: I am the magma from the Earth’s core that ignites the fire of transformation in myself and others.
name: Jess King

bio: Jess has been an athlete and leader her whole life. As a 3-year captain of her college basketball team, she motivated others through her own actions, leading her to amazing places off the court. Jess began her professional career as a school teacher who fearlessly opened new schools in underserved neighborhoods in Boston and NYC. After years in academics, Jess realized she was missing her athletic roots, and decided to leave school teaching to go back to the subject she’s most passionate about: fitness.
short_bio: “You don’t have to, you get to.”
background: I want everyone to feel like an athlete while working out, so I coach in the mindset of being in a game. I love mental breakthroughs because when we get out of our own way, out of our own head, that’s where magic happens.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'Some say my style of teaching incorporates a little bit of “tough love.” I expect a lot, but I also support a lot. Remember what you want most, and forget about what you want now.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'Outside the studio, I love boxing, lifting, going to new coffee shops in the city and spending time with my three pitbulls! I am also super excited to start training for some road races in 2019.'], ['', '']]
quote: You don’t have to, you get to.
name: Jess Sims

bio: Since his days at Art School, painting has always played an important role in Jon’s life. He’s had studio space in the UK and the US, and loves to lose himself in his art. Time flies by when he finds his flow in the studio, and that is the same headspace he loves to get into when exercising; when you're so immersed in that very moment everything else in your life just fades away. And Jon knows exactly how to get you there. With classes grounded in positivity and gratitude, Jon mixes unbeatable playlists, a wicked sense of humour and top fitness expertise to always ensure you leave each workout with a bold sense of accomplishment and a smile on your face.
short_bio: A class with Jon is an opportunity to celebrate what our bodies are capable of. A big believer that exercise should be cherished, Jon ensures his workouts show you what you can achieve with equal measures of fun and challenge along the way.
background: With my classes, I want to create a space where everyone is made to feel like they can leave doubt at the door. Let’s set those positive intentions and tick them off together as a team.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I always like to make sure exercise comes from a place of enjoyment and celebration. No matter how you feel when you turn up, the goal is to be physically and mentally happier than we were before we started.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'My huge passions outside of Peloton are painting and football. Painting offers me pure escapism and another channel to express myself - it brings me great peace.'], ['', '']]
quote: LET’S CELEBRATE YOU
name: Jon Hosking

bio: A lifelong athlete, Joslyn finds confidence in fitness and running that no one can take away. She believes exercise should be accessible for everyone and has built her career around coaching others to find the confidence to pursue their own goals and cherish their unique bodies—wherever they are on their fitness journey. A powerhouse and a self-proclaimed recovery fiend, she takes a holistic approach to training that nurtures the whole self, because her focus is firmly on the long game. Her warmth, expertise and mantra of “let’s just see” will inspire you to prove to yourself that you can do anything you set your mind to, as long as you’re willing to give it a go.
short_bio: Joslyn’s classes are spaces where everyone is free to move without judgment, whether it’s their first workout or their thousandth. She encourages you to show up as your full self and discover the power to be your own change.
background: I want everyone to know that they count, they matter. My classes are a space where you can show up as your full self and discover the power you have to be your own change.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I believe fitness is for everyone. Wherever we are on our journeys, we have these incredible bodies that can do so much right now. I want Members to realise this, whether it’s their first class or their thousandth.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'My time outside of Peloton is spent hanging with my 3 kings—my husband BJ and my two sons, Bjorn and Max. There’s nowhere I’d rather be!'], ['', '']]
quote: Let’s just see how far we can take this
name: Joslyn Thompson Rule

bio: I grew up in Silicon Valley and thought I would stay there forever. I always felt like a square peg trying to fit into a round hole when it came to my past career in tech. Deep down, I was really chasing the passion and excitement that my parents embodied in their jobs, and I'm happy to say I found that in fitness.
short_bio: Every row with Katie is infused with sincerity and warmth. She’s an expert strength coach who can flip your perspective like a switch, and her classes will always leave you feeling energized.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', "I'm excited to be with Members on this journey. It's not always going to be perfect, but it's not meant to be. At the end of the day, perfect is boring. Learning and growth? That’s where it's beautiful."], ['Outside of Peloton? ', "I have a secret TikTok life where I do makeup tutorials. I’m the girl that will get a lash on to work out. I'm a cat lover and my favorite person in the world is my grandma. If you peep my Instagram, you’ll see her too."], ['', '']]
quote: “If I can do it, you can do it, and we can do it together.”
name: Katie Wang

bio: Kendall is a natural-born fighter who empowers you to find your voice and believe in your inner strength. Kendall is a dynamic athlete, with a background in professional cheerleading, gymnastics, dance and boxing. After college, Kendall began what she believed would be a dream job at a tech startup, but soon realized the culture wasn’t the right fit for her. To cope, Kendall began boxing, where she discovered that her true calling is empowering others to break down barriers through movement and sweat. In her classes, Kendall uses the power of positive energy and rock 'n' roll to inspire you to rise up and discover your highest self.
short_bio: Kendall is a natural-born fighter who empowers you to believe in your inner strength. As a dynamic athlete, coach and creative, Kendall uses the power of positive energy to inspire you to rise up and commit to your highest self.
background: My goal is to help you discover your power. We have a choice when it comes to listening to the voice in our heads: it holds us back or helps us rise up. It just depends on how we train it.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'POSITIVE ENERGY! What we put out in the world comes back to us, so there is no time for negativity. We are all in this together for support and accountability, and I hope you enter my class feeling curious and proud.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I am a boxer at heart and have been learning the art for over 7 years. Rock ‘n’ roll seeps through my soul, especially the classics, so you can also find me listening to vinyl or scrounging up tickets to a show. '], ['', '']]
quote: Rise up and greet your higher self
name: Kendall Toole

bio: Kirra grew up on the beach in Lennox Head, Australia. She was a dancer, rhythmic gymnast and surfer through childhood and loved all the ways she could express herself through movement. Although she grew up in a spiritual household, Kirra didn’t fully dive into yoga and meditation until moving to NYC. It allowed her to feel grounded and settled in the midst of the chaotic New York energy. She’s passionate about the mental and physical challenge yoga brings and tries to make each of her classes an experience in authenticity.
short_bio: Kirra grew up in Lennox Head, Australia before landing in  New York City, and her diverse range of experiences in strength training, rhythmic gymnastics, meditation and more have shaped her into a creative and barrier-breaking instructor.
background: My passion and desire to explore the capabilities of the human body continue to evolve as I learn more and more. I love the challenge of trying to understand the mechanics and limitations of the body.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', 'Be ready to explore. Know we’re in this together, and if we put the work in, eventually we’ll get the results. I want you to leave feeling empowered and capable.'], ['Outside of Peloton?', 'Outside of Peloton, you can find Kirra practicing handstands and exploring movement. Hiking, nature and the beach ground her alongside her meditation practices.'], ['', '']]
quote: Don’t live your life to be “liked.” Live your life in your truth. Respect others and lead with your heart.
name: Kirra Michel

bio: Kirsten welcomes runners of all levels in her motivating classes. A successful career woman turned fitness instructor, Kirsten wholeheartedly embraces the changes that life brings. After seven years of working with the NFL, she shifted her focus to family. Her journey to motherhood was not easy, and fitness helped Kirsten strengthen her body and soul during difficult times. She is now the proud mother of two beautiful daughters and uses her life experiences to fuel her deeply inspiring workouts. Get lifted with Kirsten as you run together to the beats of her favorite hip hop and R&B tracks.
background: My goal in every class is to remind you that you are more than enough. If it is on your heart to do it, that means you have already been called to it. You just have to take that step, and I’ll be here right alongside you.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', 'Come as you! I coach from a place of learning from past experiences. We get comfortable in the uncomfortable. Let go of the idea of perfection and embrace your uniqueness.That is your superpower! You are a warrior. '], ['Outside of Peloton?', 'You can find me being a silly mom with my two daughters. Currently, singing and dance parties are our thing. When the babies are asleep, I’m at the gym or listening to the most ratchet music I can find.'], ['', '']]
quote: “Don’t let anyone dim your light. You were born to shine, baby!”
name: Kirsten Ferguson

bio: Growing up in small town Idaho, Kristin had big dreams of pursuing dance and acting in New York, but ended up as one of the most sought after and recognized yoga instructors in the city. Throughout her career, Kristin has been a pioneer in making yoga more accessible. Kristin has starred in yoga DVD’s, has privately trained celebrities and has written books about the value of the yoga in everyday life. As a busy mom of three boys, Kristin strongly believes that just a few minutes of yoga a day can bring more balance and harmony to your life. Kristin’s classes will challenge and ground you while bringing a strong connection back to your mind, body and breath.
short_bio: Everything you could possibly ever want, have or need is right here inside of you.
background: I really love to make yoga accessible and fun! I help people find a good flow, I love to play a great soundtrack, I like to sneak in alignment cues while keeping the pace moving. A downdog a day keeps the doctor away!
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I motivate with a smile on my face! I keep you feeling good about yourself and your body while you move through challenging poses. I want you to discover how much more you can accomplish in everything you do.'], ['Outside of Peloton', "I'm originally from Pocatello, Idaho so I love to ski! I also love to camp, hike and spend time outdoors in nature. I love the gym and pushing myself and discovering more about my body."], ['', '']]
quote: Everything you could possibly ever want, have or need is right here inside of you.
name: Kristin McGee

bio: Leanne is a former professional dancer turned fitness enthusiast who is passionate about movement and self-expression. Leanne has danced since the age of 3, and has worked her way on stage with some of the best-known artists in the world like Taylor Swift, Kylie Minogue and Katy Perry. Leanne’s style of teaching motivates you to step up, and step outside of your comfort zone. She believes that growth comes from areas of discomfort, and through her guidance and support, she’ll get you to the finish line with a smile on your face. Leanne is based in the UK and teaches live from our London studio.
short_bio: Sweat, smile, repeat!
background: I have been dancing since a very young age, so expressing myself unapologetically through music and movement is second nature. I can’t wait to channel this energy and connect with you in this way on the Bike.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I believe that music is what drives us, so I plan to curate meaningful playlists that will push and uplift you. I want you to feel supported but pushed so you get the most out of your time with me.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I love seeing new parts of the world, attending music festivals and rounding out my training through yoga and boxing. I’m always looking for a good piece of pizza or a green juice. Life’s all about balance!'], ['', '']]
quote: Sweat, smile, repeat!
name: Leanne Hainsby

bio:
Meet Logan Aldridge—a daredevil who views obstacles from all angles, helping you see challenges as an opportunity to get curious. He will push your potential and guide you to grow not only physically, but mentally. Feel embraced by his inclusive nature as he enlightens everybody that hard things really can be fun. 

Logan is an adaptive training expert, who teaches both strength classes and uniquely programmed standing and seated classes for athletes with varying physical abilities. When you train with Logan, he'll coach you through accessible and challenging workouts that will translate foundational movements on the mat into an adventurous and fulfilled life off.
short_bio: I have a unique approach to any obstacle or challenge. I see the negative but accentuate the positive. If we can have this perspective, our potential is truly endless, and growth is inevitable in all aspects of life.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I always say we train the body to sharpen the mind. When we turn obstacles into opportunities, we push through physical barriers and discover more of ourselves. We become curious about what happens if we just keep going.'], ['Outside of Peloton', "I love the outdoors, extreme sports, and adventure in general. I’m an avid snowboarder and surfer. I've got two pups—Millie and Stella. Millie is almost 5 years old. She's a mini-me tripod, and Stella is 10 years old."], ['', '']]
quote: “Tell me I can’t, and I will.”
name: Logan Aldridge

bio:
Marcel is an exceptional athlete with a background in basketball, track and field and cross country. Her time in the Army propelled her to unlock her true strength through structure and discipline. She uses this knowledge to empower her students of all levels—from the beginner to the experienced runner.

Marcel’s classes are exhilarating. Music powers her workouts, and trap and pop beats drive each interval. Marcel will motivate you as you run together to reach your next goal.
background: I aim to empower and inspire in everything that I do. That’s my mission.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', 'I live for a good challenge. I want Members to know that they don’t have to show up with all the answers but feel confident that together, as one unit, we will be relentless in ensuring they get across the finish line.'], ['Outside of Peloton?', 'I love movement. A bike ride through the borough, a hike upstate or even a walk through the park—I love being outdoors. I also love catching up with my closest friends and family to recharge and refill my cup.'], ['', '']]
quote: “Adversity introduces a man to himself.”
name: Marcel Dinkins

bio: If there’s one thing Marcel cares about, it’s that you have fun during his classes and harness your inner power. The former soccer player has learned that giving back, supporting others and being present in the moment is much more powerful than any victory. In his classes, you can expect lots of motivation and positive vibes, as well as Marcel’s contagious smile.
short_bio: Marcel wants you to have fun during your workout. The former soccer player firmly believes that giving back, supporting others and being present in the moment is much more powerful than any victory. Celebrate every workout with him.
background: Soccer has been my passion ever since I can remember. I’ve taken all that fun, that spirit and the experiences of the game with me on my journey.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I want to help you find your inner power. But most importantly, I want you to have fun. Let’s celebrate every workout together!'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I try to be present in every moment, and instead of my successes, I celebrate my experiences—walks with my girlfriend and our dog Hugo, travels or football games. My vice is ice cream. I have at least one every day.'], ['', '']]
quote: Let’s celebrate every workout together.
name: Marcel Maurer

bio: Hailing from Tampico, Mexico, Mariana grew up in a family full of athletes who drew on each other’s hard work and discipline to succeed. But as she grew older, her passion for teaching became evident as she loved helping others find their inner strength. A yoga teacher for over 11 years, Mariana has taught bilingual classes from Mexico City to NYC. Her classes are a mix of warmth, tough love and infectious energy. Her goal is to make you both smile and sweat.
short_bio: Hailing from Tampico, Mexico, Mariana will draw you to her empowering light with Spanish and English classes. With a competitive athletic background, movement, breath, energy and compassion are a huge part of Mariana’s practice.
background: I love when someone who is maybe a bit resistant to yoga takes class and feels they got as much of a workout as they did during a run, Bike ride, floor class.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', 'I try to approach with an open heart, open mind and shining heart.'], ['Outside of Peloton? ', 'Outside of Peloton, you can catch Mariana waiting in line to see the latest play or running and reading in Central Park. '], ['', '']]
quote: Experience your own resilience.
name: Mariana Fernández

bio: Matty is always eager to bring his passion for fitness and his high-energy, entertaining teaching style to the Peloton community. A born entertainer, former television reporter and pop culture guru, Matty loves to infuse storytelling and humor into every workout. Everyone should feel at-home with Matty because when you're working out with him, you're part of the family.
short_bio: "Welcome to the Body Party!" #mattysbodyparty
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I make it a party! I don’t believe that we need to suffer through our workouts. While it may not always be easy or comfortable, you’re going to be addicted to the way you feel after you’ve taken a class with me.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I watch entirely too much TV for a person who chose fitness as a career, but I promise, I’m a fitness freak! I’m also a wanderluster, theater queen, and “house head.” Odds are good I’ll probably retire on a bulldog farm.'], ['', '']]
quote: "You are not enough. You are everything!"
name: Matty Maggiacomo

bio: A former Division I distance runner with 10 years of coaching experience, Matt brings an encouraging energy grounded in athleticism to his teaching style. An avid cyclist, runner and traveler, Matt inspires Members to discover how strong they really are, and how fun training can be.
short_bio: "Train hard, train smart, and have fun!"
music_bio: Check out a sample of Matt’s current class playlist.
background: My passion is to help people. Nothing gets me more excited than helping my athletes achieve the results that they’ve dreamed of.
ordered_q_and_as:
[['How Do You Motivate?
', 'My goal is to make performance training fun! Members should come to class ready to work, and also have a good time doing it. 
'], ['Outside of Peloton
', 'Believe it or not, more fitness! Cycling, running and lifting are my favorites. I also enjoy traveling, and reading about fitness and business.
'], ['', '']]
quote: Train hard, train smart, and have fun!
name: Matt Wilpers

bio: After school, Mayla worked in Bali as a surf, fitness and yoga instructor. It was here she made her mark on the surf scene, before mentoring and motivating young women to find the confidence to make their way in the male-dominated world of surfing. Mayla now takes this spirit into her training. She loves helping people recognise their strengths and find the inner peace that comes from being comfortable in your own skin. Mayla’s personal experiences when added to her passion for fitness make her classes not only a great place to work up a sweat, but also a space to nourish the very things that make us human. Mayla works in our London studio and teaches classes in German.
short_bio: Mayla’s personal experiences in surfing and travelling when added to her natural passion for all-things fitness make her classes not only a great place to work up a sweat, but also a space to nourish the very things that make us human.
background: Every person is unique and that's what I want to celebrate in my classes. There is so much potential in each of us and my goal is to find all these treasures and bring them to the surface.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I have a strong connection to nature and the sea and I like to find parallels between the ocean and our lives. I want to inspire our members to look beyond their own horizons and discover other sides of life.'], ['Outside of Peloton', "I love water! I grew up in a small town in the north of Germany surrounded by water. I've spent half my life in the water, but only surfing has captured my heart. So as often as I can, I go surfing."], ['', '']]
quote: Every moment is yours to be enjoyed.
name: Mayla Wedekind

bio: As an experienced fitness instructor, Mila wants you to have fun in her workouts and always follow your dreams. The professional dancer has traveled the world to live her personal dream. Now, she wants to share her experiences with you and motivate and support you. With lots of positive energy and passion, she will bring out the best in you and dance with you through every workout.
short_bio: Mila wants to inspire people to follow their dreams in her workouts. As a professional dancer and trainer, she has gained experience that she wants to pass on—with lots of fun, positive energy and passion.
background: I’m so proud that I keep on living my dream as a Peloton instructor. I’ve worked hard for years for this, but it was more than worth it to be here with you today.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', "With passion and positive energy, I want to inspire others to discover themselves, live their dreams and give everything for them. It's so worth it. Even just for that feeling of happiness after every workout."], ['Outside of Peloton', "Whenever I have time, I dance. It doesn't matter if it's to hip hop or to house. I just love music and, more recently, podcasts and audiobooks too. I love diving into different worlds for hours on end."], ['', '']]
quote: Let’s redefine your limits together.
name: Mila Lazar

bio:
Nico is as versatile as her classes. The yoga trainer and meditation coach has already lived in New York, London, Berlin and Bali and has been inspired by a wide variety of cultures, teachings and yogis. Originally, she practiced yoga as a balance to her days at university in NYC but she soon discovered that yoga is much more than just a workout. Trained as a yoga teacher in Bali, Fiji, and Amsterdam, she developed her own flow which is characterized by positivity, motivation and fun. As a Peloton instructor, Nico wants you to get the best out of your training - physically and mentally.
Nico teaches her classes in German - produced in our Peloton studio in New York.
short_bio: Nico is not only a yoga trainer, but also a life coach. She enjoys incorporating this rich and varied knowledge into all her classes to give you a toolkit that will help you get the best out of you and your training.
background: Yoga is so much more than just a work-out. It's your work-in that will help you discover new ways to get more out of your workout.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate?', 'Whether you want to get fitter or more balanced - I want to give you a toolkit with yoga to master your everyday life even better. And with the right poses and the right attitude, you can achieve just about anything.'], ['Outside of Peloton', "My life is all about inspiration. Whether it's yoga, studying in New York, at home in Berlin or on holiday in Bali - open your eyes and your heart and the world will open up to you. "], ['', '']]
quote: Yoga is not just a work-out. It’s your work-in.
name: Nico Sarani

bio: Born and raised in New York, Olivia grew up playing and excelling at team sports, including lacrosse, field hockey, cheerleading and track. With a professional background in finance, as well as boxing and cycling, she brings a we-first, cheerleader approach to every class, inspiring you to leave each workout walking taller and feeling stronger.
short_bio: “Decide what you want to accomplish, and I will help you conquer it.”
background: We’re gonna work, and we’re gonna work hard. Know that I’m in this with you every step of the way. I’m a natural cheerleader, and when we workout together, we’re a team. I will always have your back, no matter how challenging things get!
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I like to lead by example. By staying with you throughout class, I can show you that sometimes, all it takes is getting out of your own way to accomplish your goals. You’re going to love the way you feel when we’re done!'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'My first word was doggy, so you can imagine what my favorite animal is! I also love fashion, family, skincare, being outdoors, and being a crazy plant lady. '], ['', '']]
quote: “Decide what you want to accomplish, and I will help you conquer it.”
name: Olivia Amato

bio:
Rad was born and raised in the Bronx, NY in a vibrant Dominican household. Soft-spoken but resilient, he found his confidence through sports and competition. Years of hard work as a boxer led him into fitness and training. 

Physical and mental strength are key in Rad’s classes, and he’ll lead you through each workout with a little tough love. His goal is to inspire others to make them feel more confident about themselves.
background: It's a beautiful thing to be able to inspire others in a way that's going to make them feel more confident about themselves. To help someone better themselves both physically and mentally is a blessing.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', 'I help you build a bigger sense of confidence. I’ll push you to find that determination within yourself, and get rid of any excuses. I make sure we have fun too, with a few dance moves and a great playlist.'], ['Outside of Peloton? ', 'I’m always trying to learn new things—whether a new instrument or how to make a new dish for dinner. I’m a huge fan of my city, so I like finding new places to eat. I’m big on spending time with friends and family too. '], ['', '']]
quote: “Lead with love. Lead with gratitude.”
name: Rad Lopez

bio: Rebecca’s background in dance, gymnastics and track & field laid a foundation for movement and body awareness that she brings to every Tread class. As a former bootcamp instructor, a Nike master trainer and much more, Rebecca aims to make every workout the best part of the day by celebrating movement and empowering through positivity.
short_bio: "Always do your best, relentlessly."
background: Celebrating movement is the most liberating and charitable thing we can do for ourselves. My goal is to create a moment in everyone’s day that excites them to get moving and enjoy the body they are living in.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'Movement is power. I’m here to empower you to do your best, every day. Challenges are not roadblocks, they’re reminders that we are stronger and more capable than we imagined, so rise up!'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I love to cook and travel! Adventure is in my blood. I love diving into culture by meeting new people, trying local food, recreating recipes from afar, conquering my fears, catching sunsets, and climbing mountains.'], ['', '']]
quote: Always do your best, relentlessly.
name: Rebecca Kennedy

bio: Peloton’s VP of Fitness Programming, Robin believes that sweat transforms lives. Her journey to Peloton came after she literally ran herself out of a successful law career. Robin is passionate about guiding Members past their limitations and excuses with inspiring, authentic anecdotes. Author of the New York Times bestseller Shut Up and Run, Robin is a RRCA-certified running coach and ultramarathoner. Her life’s mission is to redefine and rethink possibility through movement.
short_bio: "We don’t do basic."
music_bio: Ready to ride? Check out a sample of Robin's current class playlist.
background: A life lived in sweat is my mission. Every day, I work hard planting seeds for tomorrow’s greatness. The hustle in me honors the hustle in you.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'With a heavy dose of tough love because iron sharpens iron. The pride of hard work lasts longer than the discomfort. And no matter what, just keep showing up.'], ['Outside of Peloton', ' Always searching for the next best sweat, you can catch me adding up miles and increasing reps around New York City and beyond.'], ['', '']]
quote: We don’t do basic.
name: Robin Arzón

bio: Ross first discovered yoga after experiencing a sports-related injury over 20 years ago. At the time, he was barely flexible enough to touch his toes! He soon discovered the healing and transformative properties of yoga and decided to commit to the practice fully. Ross became a scholar of physical healing, diving deep into biomechanics and the inner workings of the human body. Ross has traveled to more than 30 countries to teach, and loves connecting people with diverse backgrounds through yoga. In his classes, Ross invites Members to tap into their authentic selves through movement, exploring the strength of the human spirit along the way.
background: I love yoga because it allows me to experience the world through a uniquely philosophical lens. I love to learn and absorb the different ways to approach yoga and feel most fulfilled when serving or healing others.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'We’ve all been through challenging or painful experiences in life, but by turning inwards to explore our human spirit, we can recognize that we’re incredibly powerful beings and can accomplish anything we work towards.'], ['Outside of Peloton ', 'I love to travel, and for 30 years I’ve been a certified scuba diver. I’m also a big theater buff. So much so, that I married a theater director! I’m always surrounded by incredibly talented singers and dancers.'], ['', '']]
quote: The human spirit is stronger than we know. Trust it.
name: Ross Rayburn

bio: Sam is a pro at many things but shines when it comes to motivating Members to reach their best. From the ring to the dance floor, theatre to the music room, he’s spent his life studying his two passions: fitness and the arts. After 20 years in entertainment and 15 years in fitness, Sam is ready to challenge you to go further with a perfect balance of showmanship and hustle. Sam is based in the UK and teaches live rides from our London studio.
short_bio: lorem ipsome
background: I’m a student of many different disciplines, as I know we all learn and absorb in different ways. Expect a mix of technical training, showmanship and a dash of serenity to help push you.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate?', 'I encourage Members to remember, “Why am I here?” That motivation is the element that gets us started, keeps us going and makes us want to come back for more. '], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I’m a huge film, theatre and comic buff! So you will definitely catch me at a musical, at the movies or on the couch catching up with a drama or comedy series. \r\n'], ['', '']]
quote: “Bring it. Build it. Become it.”
name: Sam Yo

bio: Selena is a unique combination of an Italian upbringing and a Hawaiian state of mind. Raised in Italy in a family of professional soccer players, sports were a way of life. When she moved to Hawaii for college, she developed a passion for surfing and for the spiritual side of fitness. Relocating to NYC, she channeled this into a career training as an amateur boxer and teaching boxing. Selena brings an empowering energy to Peloton, teaching Members how to tap into themselves to unleash their power, and accomplish goals they never thought they could achieve.
short_bio: "DREAM IT. BELIEVE IT. RECEIVE IT."
background: I believe we’re all capable of great things and that we all have that fire burning inside us. I want to share the things that have helped me access that fire, and that’s exactly what I get to do on the Peloton Tread!
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I want Members to know that I’ve got their back, always. Every day we can push ourselves to new standards, get a little stronger, run a little faster, have a little more heart and show a little more power.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'Outside of Peloton you can find me on a surfboard or in boxing gloves. There is nothing quite like the feeling of being in perfect harmony with mother nature.'], ['', '']]
quote: DREAM IT. BELIEVE IT. RECEIVE IT.
name: Selena Samuela

bio:
When Susie’s brother convinced her to enter a half-marathon, it signalled a remarkable turning point for her. Previously more often found partying than PB-ing, Susie’s gone on to become one of the most recognisable faces in the British running community, a four-time Marathon des Sables finisher and a world record-breaker for treadmill running.
It’s no wonder she believes everyone can be a runner, setting you up for success by focussing on technique, comfort and ticking off achievable goals, regardless of your age or ability. This wickedly funny Brit is all about helping you be the best version of yourself today.
short_bio: Susie sets you up for success by focussing on your technique and comfort and helping you tick off achievable goals. Because she believes everyone can be a runner, this wickedly funny Brit helps you be the best version of yourself today.
background: I believe running is for everyone. From my own experience, I know that with a little bit of self-belief, combined with the magic of putting one foot in front of the other, anything is possible. I’m here to get you to where you want to be.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate? ', 'Being the best version of yourself on the day is all you can be. If you come to push yourself, to move or to have fun, I’ve got your back, and you’ll leave with a smile on your face.'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'My family, my dogs and travelling are my favourite things … and of course running! Spare time at home is spent exploring the trails with my friends. Downtime is spent reading, cooking and eating.'], ['', '']]
quote: DON'T BE DEFINED BY OTHER PEOPLE'S EXPECTATIONS. DEFINE YOUR OWN STRENGTHS.
name: Susie Chan

bio: Tobias is a sportsman through and through. When he's not coaching triathlons, he's preparing for the next ultra-marathon, skiing, playing football, tennis, basketball or giving his all in weight training. There is only one thing that is even more important to the native of Bamberg than sport: his two children and his wife, who share his love of running with him. If you want to train with an exceptional athlete, get the best out of yourself and also grow mentally, then Tobias’s running classes are just right for you.
short_bio: For Tobias, there are no limits to running and as a former aeronautical engineer, sport is above all science for him. He is all about getting the best out of himself and finishing every workout proud.
background: Limits only exist in the mind. And I want to show our members what they are capable of. That's exactly why I became a Peloton running instructor.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'Running is connected to mental strength. I want to help others get the best out of themselves, and believing in yourself is the best motivation.'], ['Outside of Peloton', "My family is everything to me. Whether it's after an Iron Man or a normal workout, spending time with my two kids and my wife completely re-energises me."], ['', '']]
quote: Limits only exist in your mind. If you want, you can do so much more.
name: Tobias Heinze

bio: Tunde’s mission is to inspire and motivate other people to believe in the impossible. After years of struggling with her weight and self-confidence, Tunde fell in love with fitness and the doors it opened for her. Through a career as a celebrity makeup artist and brand educator, she discovered that she had a knack for teaching others to feel empowered and strong. Tunde brings an unparalleled positive energy to the Bike, fueled by personal experiences, perseverance and powerful playlists. There’s no doubt you’ll leave her classes feeling on top of the world.
short_bio: Tunde’s mission is to inspire and motivate other people to believe in the impossible. After overcoming challenging life experiences, Tunde radiates positivity and perseverance from the inside out.
background: I focus on crafting my classes with music that drives you. This rush of adrenaline allows you to move past the expectations or limitations you showed up with that day. Beyond that, I will always push you, but never let you fall.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', "I motivate from experience. I'm on a forever journey, and have been in your shoes before. I will always push you, because I know you can come up from where you are, even if you haven’t fully realized it yet. "], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I’m from Texas, so Tex-Mex and margaritas have a special place in my heart. The beach is my happy place, laughing is my favorite thing to do and I’ll never turn down the chance to strut across a dance floor! '], ['', '']]
quote: Embrace the beauty of uncertainty. It’s a place of infinite possibility.
name: Tunde Oyeneyin

bio: Growing up in a household of athletes in Chicago and majoring in kinesiology in college, Chase knew that fitness and movement would play a big role in his life. It was while working in physical therapy at a sports medicine clinic that Chase fell in love with helping people improve their lives through fitness. Chase has also worked as a personal trainer, bootcamp instructor and lifestyle coach, and brings his positive outlook and passion for helping people improve their confidence to his Peloton Tread classes.
short_bio: "It’s what you do in the dark that puts you in the light."
background: I want Members to approach my workouts by looking at the big picture. Our time together will be so much deeper than just “working out” or “being fit.” It will be about showing up to conquer what’s in front of us.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I want Members to approach my workouts as so much more than just that. This is so much deeper than just “working out” or “being fit.”'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I’m always learning. This can come in many of forms: cooking, traveling, reading, dancing, coaching, acting and more.'], ['', '']]
quote: It’s what you do in the dark that puts you in the light.
name: Chase Tucker

bio: Daniel is an empowering instructor with an electric energy. His Irish charm and unapologetic humor will have you smiling through class. A former Gaelic football player, he brings a fun, competitive spirit to every run and strength class he leads. Daniel worked hard to get where he is today. He envisioned a better life for himself and got it done with hard work and positive thinking. Daniel believes in the power of a positive mental attitude. His goal is to inspire everyone, one class at a time.
background: The Irish are known for their welcoming culture; I’m no different. I want every Member to feel at home in my workouts. I’m here to challenge you as well as make you smile. I want you to leave my class feeling empowered.
