ordered_q_and_as: [['How do you motivate? ', 'Hard work and a positive attitude got me to where I am today. I want to share that mentality with my students. You are stronger than you realize, and I will build you up mentally and physically. '], ['Outside of Peloton?', "I'm usually in the gym working out. Fitness is my life. When I do try to calm the mind and body, I dabble in photography. Editing is therapeutic for me. In my mornings off, I enjoy walking to my local coffee shop."], ['', '']]
quote: “You are stronger than you realize!”
name: Daniel McKenna

bio: Equal parts athleticism, discipline and adventure, Irène radiates a light powered by every experience that’s led her to Peloton. Growing up in Germany, Irène took dance as a way to explore her passion for movement, and through years of living, working and exploring in South Africa, she learned how to connect with people on a transformative level. Because of Irène’s diverse pursuits in fitness, business and wellness, she is a compassionate yet technical instructor, who will empower you to work hard, love hard and put yourself first. Irène is based in our London studio, and teaches in German.
background: I feel inspired when you chase your goals, no matter how much you fall along the way. What matters is that you keep going. We are all on a journey, and together we can create the strongest and healthiest version of ourselves.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'Like surfing, there will be days when you catch waves like a hero and days when you paddle for nothing. What matters is that you tried. I always want you to feel proud that you showed up for yourself—no matter what.'], ['Outside of Peloton', "I love to be outdoors! When I’m not on the Bike, I'm running, playing volleyball, lifting, hiking and finding ways new to stay balanced. "], ['', '']]
quote: “Strong mind, strong body.”
name: Irène Scholz

bio: From 5Ks to marathons and ultramarathons – since first lacing up her running shoes, Marina has finished over 80 races in 20 countries, and she’s only just getting started. A self-taught runner, she wants to make running accessible for everyone at every level and knows that with the right mindset, you can achieve anything. In her running classes, she will guide you to push yourself with each step and leave your comfort zone behind.
short_bio: As a self-taught runner, Marina wants to show you that running can be both fun and rewarding. Her classes will make you feel good and give you the confidence to achieve any goals you set for yourself.
background: The mind is always stronger than the body. If you believe that you can do it, then no one and nothing can stop you. I want to give members the confidence to succeed.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'Mindset and positive thinking are everything in running. Our bodies are capable of so much more than we can imagine. Together we will leave our comfort zones behind and reach our biggest goals!'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I love getting out and about. Whether it’s visiting flea markets and thrift stores on weekends, or going further afield and discovering remote places and new culture, nothing beats exploring.'], ['', '']]
quote: Forget records or personal bests. Feel good, believe in yourself, and start running.
name: Marina Andresen

bio: Christian Vande Velde is a former American professional cyclist who most recently rode for Slipstream Sports/Team Garmin-Sharp. Christian's impressive palmarès from his time at Slipstream include: 2008 Team Time Trial victory at the Giro d’Italia, where he become only the second American ever to don the coveted maglia rosa; 2011 Tour de France Team Time Trial win and Best Team victory; two-time top 10 Overall Tour de France finisher (2008 and 2009); 2012 overall win at the USA Pro Cycling Challenge. Christian retired from racing in 2013 and is currently a commentator for NBC and NBCSN.
short_bio: Christian Vande Velde is a member of the Team Garmin-Sharp Professional Cycling Team.
name: Christian Vande Velde

bio: Colleen Saidman Yee, whom the New York Times dubbed “The First Lady of Yoga” in 2013, brings 3 decades of experience to Peloton’s first-ever yoga programming. She opened her flagship studio, Yoga Shanti, in 1999 and, alongside her husband Rodney, partnered with Donna Karan to create Urban Zen’s Integrative Yoga Therapist Program. As both an international fashion model and widely revered yogi, she has been featured in Cosmopolitan, Vanity Fair, Oprah, and the Wall Street Journal, amongst others. In 2015, she published Yoga for Life: A Journey to Inner Peace and Freedom. Colleen lives in Sag Harbor, NY and is the proud mother of four children.
short_bio: Colleen Saidman Yee, whom the New York Times dubbed “The First Lady of Yoga” in 2013, brings 3 decades of experience to Peloton’s first-ever yoga programming.
name: Colleen Saidman Yee

bio: Growing up in Queens, New York, his father Ricardo introduced him to cycling. Hincapie quickly developed a passion for the sport and excelled, winning 10 junior national titles and two world medals prior to moving to the professional ranks and cycling's top teams. During his 19-year professional career, Hincapie was regarded as the premier American classics rider of his generation, competing in a record 17 Ronde van Vlaanderen races and finishing second at Paris-Roubaix, the best ever for any American. Beyond the classics, he rode in the Tour de France 17 times and won three US National Road Race championships.
short_bio: George Hincapie is one of the most recognized riders in the world, with numerous world championships, national championships and professional victories to his credit.
name: George Hincapie

bio: Antonia comes to Peloton as a seasoned indoor cycling instructor. She was a former Master Instructor at Flywheel Sports Chicago and also taught for SoulCycle NYC. Antonia worked in finance for 15 years before making the career change to pursue her passion in fitness. Indoor cycling gave her the opportunity to help people feel good about themselves, while strengthening their mind and body. Antonia is excited to be part of the Peloton team and help even more people throughout the world, one pedal stroke at a time. Antonia has been an avid athlete her whole life and has competed in marathons and triathlons, including the NYC Marathon and the Escape from Alcatrez Triathlon in San Francisco. She also has a background in dance, and founded the Golden Eagle Dance Team of Boston College. (That was years ago, but she is still proud of that!) You can find Antonia taking group fitness classes such as hot yoga and boxing, or catching up with friends when she is off the bike.
short_bio: 'It ain't about how hard you hit. It's about how hard you can get hit and keep moving forward; how much you can take and keep moving forward. That is how winning is done!'-Rocky Balboa
name: Antonia DeSantis

bio: California native Jennifer Jacobs is the founder and creator of J Method Fitness and a renowned international fitness instructor. Jennifer joined Peloton after spending ten years in France, where she used fitness to break through language and cultural barriers. Jennifer coaches Members out of their comfort zones, helping people accomplish things they never knew they could.
short_bio: "It's you vs. you to unleash your best self!"
music_bio: Ready to ride? Check out a sample of Jennifer’s current class playlist.
background: Empowering people is my passion. Knowing that I can help people with my knowledge and skill to reach their goals, and most of all challenge them to be their best selves.
ordered_q_and_as:
[['How Do You Motivate?
', 'This is your ride, I am just your guide. I will ask you to push yourself outside your comfort zone and try to reach a goal you never thought you could. Change does not happen in places of comfort, but rather in places of discomfort. All you need to do is try!
'], ['Outside of Peloton

', 'I love to ride my bike outdoors, especially whenever I’m back in France. I also love to study what I call the “art of boxing.” The discipline that boxers have in training from shadow boxing, bag work, skipping and circuit training each and every day, even if they get knocked down in the ring is truly admirable and something that challenges, inspires and motivates me each time I set foot in a boxing gym.
'], ['', '']]
quote: It's you vs. you to unleash your best self!
name: Jennifer Jacobs

bio:
Kim Fischer's passion for teaching comes from his desire to share the way the Peloton Indoor Cycling experience changed his life.  Kim knew he had found his bliss. Kim's classes focus on encouraging riders to set a simple intention: ride with a positive purpose and he will chase that goal right to the finish line with you.  He creates an environment that allows riders to release the negative and embrace the positive. His mind/body coaching philosophy is based on changing one's thought patterns in order to change one's life. You will leave his class with a clear-head and a sense of energized peace. He makes a killer playlist to boot! 
Originally from Oakland, CA, Kim came to NYC as a dancer and actor. He spent 2 years with Fuerza Bruta and is currently thrilled to be in the cast of Then She Fell.
short_bio: "Only the people who risk are truly free."
name: Kim Fischer

bio:
Lisa Niren joins Peloton as a Head Coach with a wealth of experience teaching indoor cycling.  Lisa developed a passion for fitness at a young age.  A life-long athlete, Lisa grew up playing competitive tennis, field hockey, basketball, and swimming.  Lisa's love for cycling began outdoors in the rolling hills of Western Pennsylvania, where she and her family often went mountain biking.  However, it wasn't until she moved to New York City to attend college at New York University's Leonard N. Stern School of Business that she became hooked on indoor cycling, with a passion that quickly led her to the instructor podium.  


After college, Lisa worked as a CPA consultant performing transaction advisory work.  Indoor cycling quickly became her "safe haven" after a grueling workday. In the saddle, she could regain clarity and composure and find the energy for the day ahead.  Lisa began teaching part time, but soon made the transition to teaching full time at Flywheel Sports.  


Lisa's classes are a high energy, calorie burning experience that challenge her riders physically and inspires them mentally and emotionally. Lisa sees each ride as an opportunity to rise above any obstacle and believes that going beyond the limits in class allows you to go beyond the limits in everyday life.


When not on a bike, Lisa enjoys wandering around the city and exploring new neighborhoods and restaurants, weight & functional training, taking barre and boot camp classes, cheering on her beloved Pittsburgh Steelers, and cooking gourmet gluten-free meals.
short_bio: "Limitations live only in our minds.  But if we use our imaginations, our possibilities become limitless." –Jamie Paolinetti
name: Lisa Niren

bio: Nicole is voracious. Convinced that we live too far from the flesh, she rides with an appetite to reoccupy the body and to brighten the mind in the discovery of new strength. Part raucous, part meditative, her rides pump with the knowledge and urgency and energy of that drive. As a triathlete and trainer, she knows the challenge of great voyages in the body; as a classically trained academic and yogi, she knows the refuge of the attentive mind. Spinning a fresh, empowering soundscape, she kindles her riders' courage, ambition, and athleticism, and celebrates the contours of their journeys.
short_bio: "There is a crack in everything...that's how the light gets in." -Leonard Cohen
name: Nicole Meline

bio: Fitness has been a part of Oliver’s life ever since he learned how to count while watching his dad do pushups at the gym. Oliver worked in London for five years as a personal trainer, and moved to New York City in 2016 to become a bootcamp instructor alongside fellow Peloton Tread instructors Rebecca Kennedy and Matty Maggiacomo. Oliver is a compassionate and charming instructor who connects with Members at every stage of their fitness journey. In classes that are accessible and easy to follow, Oliver channels his own hard work and commitment into an empathetic approach to teaching. Whether you’re pushing through challenges or celebrating a milestone, he’ll be there!
short_bio: "Failure is not falling down, but refusing to get back up.’’ We keep trying no matter what, and nothing can stop us!
background: My approach to teaching has always been: have fun! Exercise is such a wonderful thing to be able to do, and seeing people happy and proud of what they have achieved while working out with me inspires me every day to keep teaching.
ordered_q_and_as: [['How Do You Motivate?', 'I want Members to feel inspired during class, because they see me working just as hard as they are. I want them to know that I’m also feeling the burn, and we’re in it together!'], ['Outside of Peloton', 'I absolutely love learning about new cultures, so traveling is one of my favorite things to do. I’m also a total family man, so spending time with my family is very important to me.'], ['', '']]
quote: Failure isn't falling down, but refusing to get back up. We keep trying no matter what, and nothing can stop us!
name: Oliver Lee

bio:
Steph Nieman is a fitness professional and freelance consultant based in NYC and London.  She has worked with top boutique studios as an instructor, creative developer, and experience designer.  Steph studied Acting in college before moving to NYC to begin her journey as an artist.

1) What do you say while being live streamed into the homes of hundreds of Peloton riders?
Challenge the body. Challenge the mind. 
 
2) What do you consider to be the most motivating SOUND you make while coaching?
GROWL!!!  It helps me push myself to the next level... and it's really fun! 
 
3) As Head Coach, what  advice that you share with your riders?
I often encourage them to be honest with themselves, both on and off the bike. I expect them to ask the same of me. 
 
4) Side ponytail, pigtails or high and back?
Side, yo! 
 
5) Bright colors or black?
Bright for Peloton. Black for a night out. 
 
6) When does it start to hit you?
The moment I make eye contact with a rider and share a feeling of pure joy, I'm overwhelmed with a sense of passion; it hits me hard. In that moment, I remember why I do what I do. I love making people feel good, even if it is just 45 minutes of their day!
short_bio: "People don't buy what you do, they buy why you do it."  - Simon Sinek
name: Steph Nieman

bio: Steven Little has been teaching specialized indoor cycling for 10 years, and has helped launch some of the most recognizable indoor cycling studios in the country — but none have been as exciting for him as Peloton. Steven loves having the opportunity to train people everywhere through a digital experience. In his own words, “there's a kind of community that just doesn't exist anyplace else, and Peloton is the most advanced kind of indoor cycling training of its kind.”
short_bio: "You are not out of shape, you're out of practice!"
music_bio: Ready to ride? Check out a sample of Steven's current class playlist.
background: I was a Marine, and I bring a lot of what I learned while in training to the studio: focus, stamina, dedication and strength. I TRAIN riders.
ordered_q_and_as:
[['MOVING MOTIVATION
', 'As I always say, "you're not out of shape, you're out of practice." The Peloton bike is really for everyone.
'], ['GUILTY PLEASURES
', 'Tequila. On the rocks. But really, really, really good tequila.
'], ['UNIQUE CLASS STYLE
', 'I offer a very specialized type of training known as "Heart Rate Training," and will lead you into different zones throughout the class.
']]
quote: You're not out of shape, you're out of practice.
name: Steven Little

bio: Alex Howes has spent his entire four-year professional career in argyle. Hailing from Golden, Colorado the 27-year-old Cannondale-Garmin rider currently splits his time between Boulder and Girona, Spain. A former U23 Road National Champion, Alex took his first professional victory last year on the final stage of 2014 USA Pro Challenge. This season, he supported his teammates' stage and general classifications victories at Tour of Utah and Circuit Sarthe in Northwest of France. Alex is known for his scrappy style and tenacity. He favors the hilly spring classics - Amstel Gold, Flèche Wallone and Liège-Bastogne-Liège - as well as the American stage races in California, Utah and Colorado. He's highly motivated, doggedly determined and quietly capable. A fan favorite, Alex's diverse interests off-the-bike often translate into entertaining exploits.
short_bio: Alex Howes is a member of the Team Cannondale-Garmin Professional Cycling Team.
name: Alex Howes

bio: Benjamin "Ben" King is an American professional cyclist. The 26-year-old hails from Virginia and is a former U23 National Road Race and Criterum Champion and Professional National Road Race Champion (an honor he won at just 21 years old). In 2015 he won a Silver medal at the U.S. National Championships in the Time Trial and Stage 1 of Criterium International.
short_bio: Ben King is a member of the Team Cannondale-Garmin Professional Cycling Team.
name: Ben King

bio: Joe Dombrowski, a 24-year-old American professional cyclist hails from Virginia. In his first season with Cannondale-Garmin pro cycling, he won the 2015 Tour of Utah. Growing up he was a keen swimmer, played lacrosse and ran cross-country. He discovered his passion for cycling in his early teens and never looked back. Notably, racing as a junior, Dombrowski won the prestigious Girobio, the junior race to the Giro d’Italia.
short_bio: Joe Dombrowski is a member of the Team Cannondale-Garmin Professional Cycling Team.
name: Joe Dombrowski

bio: Born in New Hampshire, Ted King has been professional racing for 10 years and is currently in his 7th European professional season as a member of the Cannondale-Garmin Pro Cycling team. During his professional career, Ted raced in the sport’s biggest events including the Tour de France, Giro d’Italia, World Championships, and Monuments such as Paris-Roubaix and the Tour of Flanders. King competed in the 2013 US National Championships Road Race and landed 7th place, and also in the 2012 US National Championships Road Race and landed 3rd place.
short_bio: Ted King is a member of the Cannondale-Garmin Pro Cycling team.
name: Ted King

bio: Tom Danielson is a two-time top-ten Grand Tour finisher. He was 9th overall in the 2010 Vuelta and was the top American in the 2011 Tour de France, finishing 9th overall. That same year, the team won the Team Time Trial and netted the Best Team title at the TdF. Tom recently won the 2014 Tour of Utah for the second consecutive year, and his impressive list of palmares includes stage wins at the USA Pro Cycling Challenge and podium finishes at the Tour of California.
short_bio: Tom Danielson is a member of the Team Garmin-Sharp Professional Cycling Team.
name: Tom Danielson

bio:
George grew up in Queens, New York, where his father Ricardo introduced him to cycling. The lanky, skinny junior quickly developed a passion for the sport and excelled, winning 10 junior national titles and two world medals prior to moving to the professional ranks and cycling's top teams.
During his 19-year professional career Hincapie was regarded as the premier American classics rider of his generation. He competed in a record 17 Ronde van Vlaanderen races and finished second at the grueling Paris-Roubaix, the best ever for any American. Beyond the classics he rode in the Tour de France 17 times and won three US National Road Race championships.
short_bio: George Hincapie is one of the most recognized riders in the world, with numerous world championships, national championships and professional victories to his credit.
name: whitley locks

bio: Originally from Kansas City, Dustin attended the University Of Kansas before serving two tours in Iraq and Kuwait with the Army Reserve. After his second deployment, he moved to Chicago to experience a new city and pursue his love for fitness.  From being a three year varsity track captain as well as a squad leader in the Army, Dustin realized he had a passion for motivating people to be healthy, strong and able to perform to their utmost physical ability. Dustin worked as a certified personal trainer and group fitness instructor at Equinox in Lincoln Park and holds multiple fitness certifications include Corrective Exercise Specialist, Pre/Post-Natal, Kettlebells, and Trigger Point. Dustin’s first experience with indoor cycling was in 2013,when he participated in an indoor triathlon. Dustin was amazed by the energy and camaraderie in the studio and realized that he wanted to be a part of it, not only as a participant, but also as an instructor.
short_bio: "Persistence can change failure into extraordinary achievement." – Matt Biondi, three-time U.S. Olympic swimmer.
name: Dustin Hogue

bio: Ed is a native New Yorker and a cycling enthusiast with a passion for all things cycling related which includes indoor cycling. In addition to being a Mad Dogg spin instructor and Aqua cycling instructor. He is also a NASM certified personal trainer and races track and mountain bikes on a amateur level. Once a NYC bike messenger and a bicycle tour guide, Ed understands the value of cycling as a way of achieving and maintaining fitness especially indoor cycling which helps keep him competitive and motivated which is why he has become a Peloton Coach. Some of his favorite musical artists are Frankie Knuckles, The Roots and Nina Simone.
short_bio: "Life is like riding a bicycle — in order to keep your balance, you must keep moving." -Albert Einstein
name: Ed Hall

bio: Boston native Jon Miller is taking New York City by storm, involving himself in a variety of different pursuits, including the corporate finance world, singing and writing in the music industry, to politics. He graduated from UCLA with a degree in Political Science and enjoyed his time out in sunny Southern California but couldn’t wait to get back to his east coast roots.  His combined love of athletics and music makes him a formidable coach on the Peloton team. Jon looks to create a unique and energetic experience that will keep riders coming back for more.
short_bio:
"Nothing ever comes to one that is worth having, except as a result of hard work."
Booker T. Washington
name: Jon Miller

bio: Katie instantly fell in love with indoor cycling after she took her very first class. The loud music, and feeling of community in the studio, was so inspiring that she knew this was what she wanted to do. Katie’s love of travel has given her the opportunity to share her passion of teaching in several boutique studios across the country including JoyRide in Texas and Flywheel in Charlotte. She is very excited to be back in Chicago where it all began. Katie grew up playing team sports, and knows the importance of working together to help each other reach goals. She is thrilled to be a part of such an amazing team here at Peloton.
short_bio: "Don't miss out on something that could be great just because it could also be difficult"- Unknown
name: Katie Sido

bio:
Nikki is from Oneida, NY where she began dance as a small child.  At the age of 8 she began her study of classical ballet, trained by the Royal Academy of Dance syllabus, and performing in ballets with a youth company.  Although she enjoyed dancing and performing all forms of dance, ballet became her favorite!  

That passion for ballet led her to NYC.  To attain her undergraduate degree, she attended the New School University while dancing with the Joffrey Ballet program. While in college, she still found time, to dance on MTV’s Direct Effects- a live daily broadcast.  After graduation, she decided to further her studies in dance, and then received her masters degree in dance, with an emphasis on choreography and composition at NYU's, prestigious Tisch School of the Arts.  

After graduation, she quickly started receiving jobs with small dance companies in the city.  She began dancing principal roles in ballets, such as the Sugarplum Fairy in the Nutcracker, Princess Aurora in Sleeping beauty, and Snow White, to name a few. While keeping up with her performing schedule, Nikki began to expand her repertoire as a choreographer for stage, film, and music videos.   She has also choreographed commercials for Old Navy and Barney's Co Op.   
Nikki became passionate about yoga, while recovering form a dance injury, and received her 200hr teacher training certificate at Yoga Works in NYC.  Teaching yoga and dance in the city led her to uncover another love- fitness indoor cycling.  Nikki has a passion for teaching and helping people attain goals they aspire to achieve.  Nikki is very excited to put her fitness, dance, music, and creative experience to use on a Peloton bike.  She wants people that take her class to paint a mental landscape, and journey with her towards their fitness goals!
short_bio: "Live not one's life as though one had a thousand years, but live each day as the last." -Marcus Aurelius
name: Nikki Nasto

bio:
ELLA KAY is one of NYC's hottest fitness coaches redefining the industry on a global scale. Kay's dynamic approach to life and fitness is inspired by her work with world-renowned companies including Cirque du Soleil.  She works "in the studio" teaching both magnetically powerful classes and personalized private sessions. Outside of the studio, Kay's work developing methods and branding for top luxury boutique fitness studios has revolutionized the industry.  From New York to London to Bogotá and beyond, she has coached some of the finest acrobats, athletes, stars, and public figures. 

Kay is a coach, fitness model, dancer, adventurer, and athlete with a dynamic zest that will elevate you to new levels of physical potential.  You can catch her strutting around with her Toy Fox Terrier, Lille, near their West Village residence, coaching a ride at the elite NYC Peloton Studio, or anytime you clip-in on your sleek at-home Peloton Bike. 

Poise. Passion. Pride. Progression.
short_bio: "The vision of a champion is bent over, drenched in sweat, at the point of exhaustion, when nobody else is looking." --Mia Hamm
name: Ella Kay

bio:
James has been a leading fitness instructor and private trainer in the New York area for the past 15 years. He received his education from University of Michigan and before fitness, spent over 10 years in advertising with Young & Rubicam and Ogilvy Worldwide. James has an extensive background in cycling, martial arts, private training and yoga. As a Master Cycling Instructor and Trainer, James has taught group fitness internationally and state side at both full-service fitness centers and dedicated studios. In 2008, James founded THE STUDIO - an indoor cycling and private training gym in New York City bringing an integrated approach to fitness. 

Originally a competitive cyclist, James brings an outdoor cycling experience to his classes and makes the music a "HUGE" part to his classes. James blends an eastern and western approach to his teaching and believes in working past all physical, emotional and mental limits through inspirational, empowering and fun hardcore workouts! James resides in Tribeca, New York, the French West Indies and Montauk, New York with his amazing wife Patricia, son Gunner and daughter Devon. When he is not on a bike you can usually find him on the links... FORE!
short_bio: "Count your blessings. Once you realize how valuable you are and how much you have going for you, the smiles will return, the sun will break out, the music will play, and you will finally be able to move forward the life that God intended for you with grace, strength, courage and confidence." - Og Mandino
name: James Park

bio: Described as having “legs of blinding speed perfectly choreographed and set to music with heart-thumping rhythms of inspiration,” Rhodie Lorenz has been hooked on the intensity and inspiration of indoor cycling for more than 15 years!  On the bike and off, Rhodie is swift, passionate and purposeful. She co-founded JoyRide Cycling Studio (in Westport, Darien and Ridgefield, Conn., and San Antonio, Texas) and developed its exclusive method based on her belief that form (based on Pilates principles) + attitude (best positive effort) + good music (rhythm and mood) = a better you. Rhodie has an innate ability to motivate riders to push past their fitness abilities and overcome challenging climbs in the studio and in everyday life. She leads riders on heart-pounding fitness journeys, while helping them build their confidence, relieve stress and feel healthier than ever before. Many of her best classes have been choreographed on her kitchen dance floor with her three young, music aficionado sons!
short_bio: Rhodie Lorenz is a co-founder of and coach at JoyRide Cycling Studio.
name: Rhodie Lorenz

bio: Moses is a certified Spin™, TRX™ and SYNCcycling™ Instructor with an ear for beat. Born in upstate NY, he was raised across the American and Canadian east coast and the southern US. Finding his passion for fitness through the modeling industry, to him, cycling is therapeutic as well as a journey. Moses’ classes are challenging and uplifting. His passions include rowing, holistic living, vegan bodybuilding and bodyweight training.
name: Moses Daniel

bio:
Ary Nuñez is an internationally renowned fitness expert, media personality, Nike sponsored athlete and celebrity personal trainer. A New York native and proud Latina, she is the founder/owner of Gotham Global Fitness, a company founded on the principles of Eastern and Western philosophies of training the human form. Her fitness background is in the martial arts (she is black belted in Karate, Tae Kwon Do and Kung Fu, and has studied in a total of seven art forms), dance, and western athletics.

Calling herself a "modern day ninja," Ary teaches her "Gotham Orchestra" of group fitness classes at exclusive global and national fitness facilities and privately trains clients including celebrities: Rihanna, Kat De Luna, Alicia Keys, and David Tutera.

A popular media personality, Ary has hosted health and wellness segments for major television networks including ESPN, Discovery Channel, NBC, ABC, CBS, FOX, Univision, Telemundo, MTV, and A&E. She is currently working in parternship with Turner Broadcasting on Upwave, a new multi-platform health and wellness entertainment brand that will deliver a digital and linear healthy living destination to consumers and advertisers and is in development of her own radio and internet show called ArysAmerica.
She has consulted with major brands and corporations such as Nike, NFL, Nintendo, Nestle, Healthfirst, The Mondrian Oriental, Soho House, Glaxo Smith Kline, Pfizer, Cunard and Princess. She speaks internationally and has been featured in fitness videos, print ads, commercials, independent films, reality/documentaries and theatre performances - bridging art, evolution and fitness.

Ary is the founder of Generation PHYT 
(Personal Health Youth in Training). This not-for-profit advocacy group uses health and fitness to empower kids and boost self-esteem. Ary is an active member, volunteer and advocate with many charitable causes including the American Heart Association, Girl Power, and Mental Health Power!
short_bio: "I Say. I Do. I Am"
name: Ary Nuñez

bio:
Marion Berrian Roaman has been totally and completely devoted to indoor cycling since she first discovered it at her local gym in Boulder Colorado.  As a chef with her own catering company, Marion no longer had time to go for her six hour rides in the mountains.  Discovering indoor cycling completely changed her life.  Marion's addiction to indoor cycling quickly became obsessive.

"I found I was going to class at 6am, 12:30pm and 6:30pm.  It had began to interfere with my career."

As a bold 27 year old, Marion sold her half of the catering company, moved back to New York and opened the first indoor cycling boutique in New York.  As much as she loved running the business and all that entailed, at the end of the day it all came back to the teaching.

"No matter how difficult the day was or how tired I felt or how afraid of was of dealing with competition, I always had that bike.  I always came back to teaching. I have been through some really tough stuff in my life. The combination of the energy in the room, the music and the passion for fitness is what has always gotten me through."

Marion taught at the major New York fitness clubs as well as her own studio, ZoneHampton. In 2011, Marion sold her business to Flywheel Sports where she taught for three years as a Master Instructor. 

Marion is beyond excited to be joining the team at Peloton as Co-Founder and General Manager where she will be coaching rides, directing global content and building the Peloton Community.
short_bio: "Think globally, ride locally."
name: Marion Berrian Roaman
